{
  "stem": "9601.7",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, this last week [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] was very stressful.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I thought and re-thought how should I say my story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How should explain the cruelty and the humanity that were brought upon a group of people who have behaved like human beings in the village and yet by their very neighbors were so decimated?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A little girl of four, a little girl of six or seven, the old, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the women.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I regard women much nicer than men in their behavior to humanity, yet they met such an ugly death.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very difficult not to cry or not to feel sad and feel angry when people go out in the public and deny that such a thing happened.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Yet my neighbors from the Ukraine, from [INAUDIBLE] who I correspond with, acknowledge in their letters what a difficult time we had.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had a difficult time too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't deny that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were not annihilated as a people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If Olga lost a brother, her mother survived, her sister survived, her uncle survived, her grandparents survived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In my case, if it wasn't for their generosity, I wouldn't be here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My grandma with her grandchildren, as with her daughter, did not deserve to die a death like that, to be smashed by a gun or be smashed by a two by four.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then their teeth pulled out just because they had dental works.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And who knows what else they were robbed of.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Yet they lie in an unmarked grave among bushes where animals tread.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Not right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We all people have the same religious root, yet some of us disregard it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's not fair.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
